The Lake Victoria Basin Commission next week will celebrate its 10th anniversary. Executive secretary Ally-Said Matano said the celebrations will be at Tom Mboya Labour College on November 12.LVBC is an institution of the East Africa Community and is mandated to promote sustainable development of the Lake Victoria Basin.It became operational on April 2006 after a declaration by the EAC Council of Ministers. The theme of the event is: &ldquo;Ten years of sustainable development through partnerships.&rdquo;